⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Nostradamus
node N1 · N1 · ⟦Nostradamus:N1:26055b⟧

WHO   — Nostradamus — the seer of Salon
WHAT  — The archetype of the Western seer — author of the Centuries, the most enduring book of prophecy ever written; revered and debunked in equal measure across five centuries.
WHERE — N1 · Nostradamus  Framework inputs: Les Propheties (1555)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because he believed a divine fire could show a man the shape of things to come; because to speak it plainly was to risk the Inquisition, so it had to be veiled; because a prophecy obscure enough can never quite be proven wrong.
HOW   — By judicial astrology and the night rite of the brass tripod and the bowl of water; by a verse so allusive — French, Latin, anagram, omen — that it bends to any age that reads it.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I wrote the future in the dark, in riddles — so that it could be read forever, and proven never.

